article.headline: UMKC 82, Centenary 70
article.story: KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Carlton Aaron had 31 points and 14 rebounds to lead Missouri-Kansas City to an 82-70 win over Centenary on Monday, giving the Kangaroos their ninth straight victory. Aaron was 13-for-15 from the floor and scored 21 of his career-high 31 points in the first 20 minutes of the game, but UMKC (9-7, 7-0) trailed 30-29 at halftime. The Kangaroos took control of the game early in the second half with a 19-7 run in the first 5:28. Aaron gave UMKC its first lead of the game at 31-30 with 19:01 left when he hit an inside shot. The Kangaroos shot 60 percent (18-of-30) from the field in the second half after shooting just 39 percent (10-of-26) in the first half. UMKC also outrebounded the Gentlemen (2-16, 0-7) 39-28 overall. Mike English, who had eight points for the Kangaroos in the decisive run, scored 16 of his 17 points in the second half. English also had 13 rebounds and five assists. Quinton Day added 17 points for UMKC, and Tim Blackwell had 10. Centenary got within six at 76-70 on 3-pointer from Tyrone Hamilton with 1:06 left, but the Kangaroos connected on 6-of-8 from the free-throw line to seal the victory. Hamilton led the Gentlemen with 19 points. Chad Maclies had 15 points and seven rebounds for Centenary. Kevin Taylor added 11 points, and Jarmorrow Moragne had 10.
